President Cyril Ramaphosa is in the hot seat at the State Capture Inquiry today. JOHANNESBURG - ANC President Cyril Ramaphosa is testifying before the State Capture Inquiry. Ramaphosa's testimony is being divided into two parts. READ: Ramaphosa to testify at State Capture Inquiry The focus on the first two days of his appearance is on ANC issues and cadre deployment. He will then appear again next month to speak as the president of the country.